name: St. Eustace White
summary: Eustace White was an English Catholic priest and martyr who was executed during the Elizabethan persecution. He was ordained in Rheims and returned to England to minister secretly to Catholics. He was arrested, tortured in the Tower of London, and eventually hanged, drawn, and quartered at Tyburn. He is one of the Forty Martyrs of England and Wales and is remembered for his courage and faithfulness despite severe torture.
